original: Härenstam, Alida Elsa, seminarieadjunkt, Norrköping, f. 26/1/07 i Gamileby, Kalm. 1., av Herbert Malmberg o. Sigrid Andersson. G. 39 m. fil. dr Curt Härenstam. Barn: Magnus f. 41, Agneta 44. — Stud:ex. i Linköp. 26, teol. fil. ex. i Gbg 27, teol. kand. 33, fil. kand. 38, provår 39-40. Stud:-resa t. Tyskl. 28. Tjg. v. Gamleby o. Värnamo folkhögsk. samt Eksjö o. Lunds h. a. 1., adj. v. Tomelilla sämre alisk. 41, numera adj. v. Norr köp. småsk :sem.
translated: Härenstam, Alida Elsa, seminar teacher, Norrköping, born January 26, 1907 in Gamileby, Kalmar County Sweden, daughter of Herbert Malmberg and Sigrid Andersson. Married in 1939 to Doctor of Philosophy, Curt Härenstam, and has two children: Magnus born in 1941 and Agneta born in 1944. Alida passed her studentexamen (high school) in Linköping in 1926, her theology fil. ex. (bachelor's degree) in Gothenburg in 1927, her theology kand. (master's degree) in 1933, and her fil. kand. (bachelor's degree in philosophy) in 1938. She also completed one year of teaching practice in 1939-1940 and went on a study trip to Germany in 1928. Alida has worked as a teacher at Gamleby and Värnamo folk high schools as well as Eksjö and Lund h. a. 1.. She was a seminar teacher at Tomelilla sämre alisk. in 1941 and is presently working as a seminar teacher at Norrköping småsk.
